news.title: L&T Realty Developers to sell its entire stake in Think Tower Developers
news.para: "L&T Realty Developers Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of Larsen & Toubro Ltd, has entered into an agreement to sell its entire stake of 99 per cent in Think Tower Developers Private Ltd, a subsidiary company (TTDPL), on January 5," Larsen and Toubro (L&T) said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Merge old & new property IDs by January 8: ULB to Gurugram civic body
news.para: Varshney directed that data integration of the old and new property IDs be done by January 8, since chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar will review the status of the work on January 10.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC tells RWAs to go to government before court
news.para: An HC division bench comprising Justice Harinder Singh Sidhu and Justice Lalit Batra passed these orders while disposing of a plea filed by Corporate Green Buyers Welfare Association against the DLF regarding a housing project in Gurgaon.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder had roped in another firm in Rs 27 crore cheating case
news.para: Developer Jagdish Ahuja was detained and brought from Punjab to Mumbai on December 16, by the city EOW. He was arrested in a Rs 27 crore cheating case for allegedly duping several flat buyers.

news.title: Father-son duo dupe man of Rs 10 crore in builder scam in Mumbai
news.para: Complainant Mukesh Agarwal who is a real estate consultant and also deals into logistics, lodged an FIR with the Borivli police on January 2.

news.title: Yashasvi Group buys Navkar Institute building in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ahmedabad-based Yashasvi Group has purchased the Navkar Institute building. Its promotor, Jigar Bharwad, confirmed the deal but refused to share details of the deal size.

news.title: Maharashtra: 78 property registration officials under government lens
news.para: Of the 78 officials listed, 44 are from Pune, 23 from Thane, eight from Aurangabad and three are from Latur. Latest data available with the department showed that 13,920 property documents from Pune, Thane, Aurangabad, and Latur were under the scanner.

news.title: No violation of project layout in Jaypee Greens, Greater Noida tells HC
news.para: According to the RWA, the developer promised to construct an 18-hole golf course spread over 193 acres for the residents, but many commercial and residential projects came up on the 49 acres in the past 4-5 years, and the golf course shrunk to 144 acres.

news.title: NCLAT upholds NCLT order dismissing Wave Megacity's plea to initiate insolvency against itself
news.para: ​​The insolvency appellate tribunal observed that the company's plea to initiate insolvency proceedings against itself under Section 10 of the IBC was with "malicious purpose" and "was to save the Corporate Debtor from liabilities, responsibilities and prosecution".

news.title: CBI books HDIL promoters in fresh case of Rs 140 crore bank fraud
news.para: The bank has alleged that Guruashish Construction was a wholly-owned subsidiary of Housing Development and Infrastructure Limited (HDIL) engaged in the real estate business in Mumbai.

news.title: Now, YEIDA to develop 'fintech hub' in sector 7
news.para: YEIDA CEO Arun Vir Singh said that EY has already completed a study of Fintech hubs in India and abroad and suggested a way forward for establishing one on YEIDA land.

news.title: Power supply to be suspended to 100 illegal brick kiln units Coimbatore
news.para: Sources said many illegal units came up in these locations after the district administration initiated closure proceedings against brick kilns in the Thadagam region in 2021 as they were polluting the surrounding environment.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Plots of land distributed to nearly 11,000 poor families in Tikamgarh
news.para: His government will ensure that no person lives in a 'kaccha' (temporary) house in the state and provide residential plots to all eligible persons, Chouhan said on Wednesday.

news.title: Bengaluru: New ray of hope for forgotten Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout
news.para: If the Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) Commissioner’s visit to Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout (NPKL) is any indication, it seems the BDA has decided to bring cheers to hapless people who bought sites there.

news.title: About 50,000 beneficiaries return their house plots to Andhra Pradesh government
news.para: Beneficiaries are among the 30.3 lakh people who were given house sites by the government. Those who returned the plots said they were either located close to burial grounds or were too far from their present habitations.
